ommunity operates and functions in Besat high school and Koshan high school and how the principal's leadership supported the development and maintenance of a professional learning community.Participants included two principals and ten teachers from these two schools.Data were collected through interviews with two principals and ten teachers and analyzed by hand-coding.Interviews and observations at these two case-study schools showed that although these two schools represented two different levels,I found many similarities in these schools.Sharifi,the principal of Besat High School,focused on professional learning community practical implementation,approaching topics such as time,group structuring,school context,and institutional plan attentiveness.On the other hand,Mohasil,the principal of Koshan High School,addressed more subjectively about professional learning community formation,such as when he argues about sharing views on education.Also,findings indicated that the principal is a transformational and instructional leader and can recognize leadership qualities in others.It is essential to the development and maintenance of a professional learning community.So the result of a leadership team is central to the overall success of a professional learning community;communication and collaboration are related to the development and maintenance of a professional learning community.They are practical tools for developing a better learning organization,and a learning organization that promotes growth,learning,and empowerment relates to the success of a professional learning community.
