d distributive leadership models with‘management by working’;this was a style which saw the school principal getting involved in assignments and also being keen on monitoring and supervision.Also,the findings affirm that the leaders used transformational and transactional models together in one approach,this was then coined as‘transfor-sactional model’.This saw the holistic development of the students in their quest to education.The study developed a‘Student Educational Outcome Model’.This model is based on the impact of school principals,and presents two significant factors affecting students’educational outcomes in high schools.The study in its conclusion states that,the principals revealed an outstanding practice through their various educational leadership styles to create a learning environment for students.In the study’s recommendation,similar or related study can be conducted using different research approach to solicit more responses from participants.This research further accentuates that there is the need for an in-depth educational background for principals at least master’s degree clutched with experience and innovative minds which must be the yardstick for employing principals in such a result-oriented generation.
